{
  "doc_id": "20472",
  "text": "• OZ 277, Arterolane ™ , (a phase-4 compound); another synthetic peroxide is the most advanced of the new anti-malarials. Combined with piperaquine, this new drug is already registered and marketed by Ranbaxy in India [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . There is a concern that OZ277 shares cross-resistance with the artemisinin derivatives. High resistance levels against the partner drug piperaquine have already been documented in Cambodia and Vietnam. A further concern is the QTc prolongation observed in 6.9% of study participants [CITATION_4] .",
